yeule, the cyborg alchemist coalescing the soundscapes of glitch-pop electronica, alt rock, and trip-hop. After their breakthrough sophomore album in 2022, Glitch Princess, Nat Ćmiel crystallised their place as alt electronica luminary with their boundary-breaking 2023 album softscars. Both albums were named Best New Music by Pitchfork with the latter lauded as a “riotous, high-energy journey” by the Guardian. With their forthcoming work, yeule paints us a picture with divine poise: fragmented shards of their persona non grata, or "darker side," pieced together as the painterly fatale who burns through the canvas of post-modernity. With visual artworks captured by artist Vasso Vu, Ćmiel is seen here tethered to their role as a "painter" before performer. yeule, reincarnated again as a haunting facsimile of their past in Evangelic Girl is a Gun. Ćmiel paints an homage to the artist’s role—an artist that illuminates the neon glow of an ego death, and the transformative forms of love, immortalising in our physical reality, their dream within all dreams.

Plunging into the mysterious and creatively-free world of Japanese record label DD Records. Founded by Kamada Tadashi in the early 1980s. The collective produced hundreds of cassette releases from their wider social and creative circle, like-minded in their disregard for genre restrictions and commerciality. 
Selected and mixed by NTS, featuring tracks from Phantom Limb's forthcoming reissue, Disk Musik: A DD. Records Compilation.

DJ, artist and techno impresario, Word of Command welds fevered collage and high-octane techno into a hallucinatory dreamscape. He is the founder of FIST (@funisstilltransgressive), a queer techno party that pays tribute to radical fun, while engaging the visibility of communities of otherness through techno in NYC.
TRiNH - an hour of covers and nostalgic feels, playing a wide range of genres with a focus on L-O-V-E.
Cuban record collector, ethnomusicologist researcher, picks up a hour of global vinyl via Havana every months.
Forager Records is a Los Angeles based record label, committed to unearthing and breathing new life into rare and under appreciated sounds from the past.
A Colourful Storm from label head Moopie, featuring contemplative ambience, folksong and indie-pop melancholia, contemporary electronics and beyond.
Avant-garde musician and composer Jim O'Rourke pulls stops by once a month, pulling an hour of picks from his extensive record collection.
Monthly enqiuries into encounters in harmony, forms of hearing, and occasionally responding.
New releases and current inspirations from your hosts Jonnine Standish and Nigel Yang aka HTRK.

nts2.n: Perfect Lives and Tezez Tapes: On the Horn - Tapes from Eritrea and Ethiopia
nts2.d:
Record, book and ephemera dealers Perfect Lives link up with archival Eritrean cassette label, Tezez Tapes, for On The Horn. 
Semir from Tezez Tapes shows off their archive in the first hour, with cassettes from 1985-’91, as mostly diasporic Eritrean artists were experimenting with synthesizers, drum machines, and other modern production techniques to recontextualise traditional melodies and songwriting. Perfect Lives step up in the secon dhour with a mix of Eritrean and Ethiopian pop music from their store selection.

Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!
